Authorization in this system is centralized and tenant-aware, designed to answer a single question for every sensitive operation: whether an authenticated user is allowed to perform a specific action on a given resource within a specific tenant. Authentication and tenant context are resolved upstream at the API Gateway, and the Authorization Service receives only trusted, server-derived inputs (user ID, tenant ID, action, and resource). Authorization is enforced before any state-changing operation, follows a deny-by-default policy, and applies consistently across all services to prevent privilege escalation, IDOR, and permission drift. The service is stateless, internal-only (gRPC), and contains no business logic or data mutation, ensuring clear separation of concerns, reduced attack surface, and predictable, auditable access control aligned with Zero Trust principles.
